subSubSection.paragraph:
Aedeagus (
Fig. 8
) main-piece with very large pointed process on right side, with a small process issuing from its base (visible in lateral view); left paramere widest subbasally, then tapering to narrow tip, setae very sparse, in a row on ventral margin; right paramere markedly arcuate, setae clustered at tip; gonopore bearing flagellum long. Female last tergite without incisions, with two transverse ridges, setae slender, tapering; gonocoxite and spermatheca as illustrated (Figs. 209, 229).
